BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 28 Apr--On 28 April, Foreign Minister 
Andrzej Olechowski described the main directions of Polish 
foreign policy as security and Poland's relations with NATO and 
the West European Union, tighter relations with the European 
Union, a more active policy toward the East, and cooperation 
with neighboring countries. 
  Olechowski, who arrived at the Sejm to present the main 
directions of foreign policy to deputies from the Sejm Foreign 
Affairs Commission, said that these four priorities are of equal 
importance. The meeting is closed to the press. 
  The Sejm will debate foreign policy on 12 May. 
  Deputies will also discuss a draft statement on the revival 
of imperial and hegemonic trends in Russia. 

